https://www.quora.com/Who-are-some-famous-misanthropes-either-real-or-fictional
Who are some famous misanthropes, either real or fictional?
	11 Answers
	Abhinav Maurya
	Abhinav Maurya, PhD Student (Machine Learning, Public Policy) at CMU
	Updated Jul 24, 2012 · Author has 540 answers and 1.4m answer views

    Ludwig Wittgenstein: regarded to be one of the most important philosophers of the twentieth century
    Friedrich Nietzsche: another well-known philosopher
    Martin Heidegger: philosopher
    Søren Kierkegaard: philosopher
    Jean-Paul Sartre: writer and philosopher; known to have said "Hell is other people."
    Franz Kafka (author): highly regarded German writer
    Oscar Wilde (author): well-known English writer; known to have said "Other people are quite dreadful. The only possible society is oneself."
    Patricia Highsmith: American novelist and short-story writer whose works have been adapted into movies like Strangers On A Train (1951), The Talented Mr. Ripley (1955), Ripley's Game (1974) and Edith's Diary (1977).



